race.comment: SMART MINX (1) had a tough draw to overcome and was game in defeat when only a nose from Tiny Sniffy in second (22.44) at this track. Well placed and gets her chance. REBORN SPARK (7) hit the ground running from a squeeze draw and was prominent throughout but faded out of it when 6th at Richmond in a Grade 5. A forward showing wouldn't surprise. LIGHTNING BLITZ (2) produced a modest effort most recently when seventh at The Gardens over 400m behind Lizzie Long Legs (23.88) in a Grade 5. One of the better hopes. MCCATHERY (6) has ability and can feature with the right run after missing a cheque here most recently.
